Dickson Njanja Mararo the suspect behind the shooting of two police officers and a woman at Quiver’s Lounge in Nairobi, last Friday, has surrendered to police. Mararo aged 28 years presented himself to the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) headquarters Monday afternoon accompanied by lawyer Cliff Ombeta. The suspect is set to be charged with attempted murder. A Glock semi-automatic pistol and 38 rounds of 9mm ammunition were recovered from the suspect. Dickson Njanja Mararo the suspect behind the shooting of two police officers and a woman at Quiver’s Lounge in Kasarani, last Friday, has surrendered to detectives at DCI headquarters. The suspect who is currently being grilled by Serious Crimes detectives pic.twitter.com/sOiii2p2ac — DCI KENYA (@DCI_Kenya) July 5, 2021 Also Read:  The incident occurred following an argument over a woman. One of the police officers sustained a gunshot on his neck while the other was shot on the hand. Video Of The Day: KEMRI scientists examine safety of anti-malarial drugs in first trimester of pregnancy